race.comment: Tough race with many struggling for their best. INQUISITOR (5) is coming off an uncharacteristic poor run when he just didn't come on last time over further. Back in trip and has obviously done well because he's on the quick back-up. Previous form excellent for this and well worth another chance. RUBAAHY (8) was a close-up fourth two back then thereabouts in the latest in tougher company. Returns home and is a course and distance winner. Gets a chance to find form. JOHNNY THE KID (7) is another coming off a poor run last time. Drops in grade, drops in trip, senior rider goes on and is drawn well. Should be at top now in the first campaign for the new yard and won't get a better chance to feature. ITZA MOTZA (2) is going along well finishing runner-up this grade last time and only needs to run up to recent efforts to feature. MISS HIGHFALUTIN (9) is coming off a maiden win and although skips a grade has upside and can run well again.
